I'm working on an embedded C++ project for an automotive ECU and we're seeing a slow RAM exhaustion during long-duration stress tests. It looks like a leak, but I can't find the specific allocation. 

Here is the main telemetry loop:

```cpp
void process_sensor_data(SensorData* data) {
    if (data->is_valid()) {
        TelemetryPacket* packet = new TelemetryPacket(data);
        log_packet(packet);
        // Sometimes we skip logging if the bus is busy
        if (bus_status == BUS_BUSY) {
            return; 
        }
        delete packet;
    }
}
```

The heap grows by about 4KB every hour. Can you give me a systematic approach to finding where these allocations are failing to free?

